Re: Possible claim for excess proceeds from a California tax-defaulted property sale

Dear {{ owner_name or "Property Owner" }},

Our records indicate that property associated with {{ county_name }} County, California may have generated excess proceeds after a tax-defaulted property sale. Under California Revenue and Taxation Code sections 4671 through 4675, excess proceeds are the funds that remain after the county applies sale proceeds to delinquent taxes, penalties, costs, and other amounts allowed by law.

The property reference we have is:
